        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on Huxley–Falconer dispute [see "On the method of palaeontology", <hi rend="italic">Ann. &amp; Mag. Nat. Hist.</hi> 18 (1856): 43–54].</p>  
<p>Wollaston’s <hi rend="italic">On the variation of species</hi> [1856].</p> 
            <p>Has exploded to Lyell against the extension of continents.</p>
            <p>Plants common to Europe and NW. America as result of temperate climate.</p>
